<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-10-18T20:30:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-10-17T00:00:00-05:00" n="398" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d398">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">012.3/7849: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Algiers (<persName type="from">Cole</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Algiers</hi></placeName>, <date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" notAfter="1942-10-18T20:30:00-05:00" notBefore="1942-10-17T00:00:00-05:00">undated</date>.<lb/>[Received October 18, 1942—8:30
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>691. For Admiral Leahy from Murphy. You might be interested in
                                knowing that Darlan’s son, Alain, has just entered an Algiers
                                hospital and according to present diagnosis he is suffering from
                                infantile paralysis.</p>
                            <p>Repeated to Tuck. [Murphy.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Cole</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>